column2: Heavy rain in last 24 hours- small chop- mostly cloudy- blue-green algae
Hot- sunny- blue-green algae bloom- fish kill affecting mostly small fish- e.g.- 4-5" walleye- small bluegill- etc.
light algae is more dense here. Not bad for this time of year- cormorants and gulls
Partly cloudy- heavy rains in last 24 hours- more algae than deep hole
North end of lake has lots of cormorants on islands and marshes
same as above 0903- green fuzz is heavier here- no boats here today- some local mallards
Strong SE winds (15+).  Clouds moved in and wind picked up after taking samples at Denning point.  Air temp ~61 degrees.  Pelicans- cormorants- gulls- ducks- etc.
NE wind- cloudy- moderate algae bloom- no rain in last 2 weeks.  Lake is low.
Sunny- calm- hot (90)- blue-green algae.  Heavy rain (5" + ) 5 days ago.  Unusual number of gulls but no obvious fish kill.  Pelicans have left.
Sunny- warm- very breezy around 15mph.  No fishermen out.  More algae present than at Denning point.
Light NE Breeze- many pelicans- cormorants- some diving ducks- no vegitation- about 60 degrees F- sunny.
Partly sunny- west wind- low 80's- very few fishermen- no major algae bloom yet this year....very strange.  No June report due to flood conditions.
Sunny- NE wind 5-7mph- a few fisherman- no serious algae bloom so far this year.
No vegetation- no blue green algae- very light green algae- no birds
6 feet of water.  No vegetation.  Some common gulls.  Some cormorants.  Some boats on the lake.
Sunny- SW breeze- slight chop- few fishermen- ducks- cormorants- gulls.  Not much alge and no major algae bloom so far this year.
Mostly sunny- calm- no algae- very clear water.  Pelicans- ducks- cormorants.  A few fishermen.
Sunny- warm- light wind.  Several fishermen.  Fishing has been very poor all summer.  No pelicans- only a couple of cormorants.  Lake is 'pickle' green but no floating algae.
lots of boats.  swimmers using lake today.
Sunny- light SW breeze- very few fishermen- algae forming- 80 degrees
NW breeze- no fishermen- moderate algae bloom
Mostly sunny- warm- light chop- no fishermen- lots of pelicans.
I did not see any amount of pelicans- cormarants- ducks or geese.  Lots of pleasure boats and several fishermen.  75*- east wind 10 mph- sunny.
Mostly sunny.  Good number of fishermen- pelicans- slight algae bloom- 75- S wind 5mph- slight chop.
Cloudy- hot.  SW breeze- a few fishermen- a number of recreational boaters- plenty of ducks- cormorants and pelicans.
Sunny- calm- lots of pelicans and cormorants.  Only a couple of fishermen.
Sunny- 70 degrees- light north wind- log of pelicans- some cormorants- a few fishermen
Sunny- light NE wind- 75 degrees- lake is low and no rain in weeks.  No fishermen except commercial crew.  A few pelicans and cormorants.  Very mild algae bloom.
Sunny 74- light NW breeze- algal bloom- only 2 boats on the lake- lots of pelicans on north end- a few cormorants.
Sunny- NE wind 5-10- 61 Degrees- no fishermen- no pelicans- lots of gulls- high winds 15-20 nw previous 2 days.
75- Sunny- light south breeze- only a few fishermen- 100-s of pelicans but only a few cormorants.
74- Cloudy- 1.3 inches rain in the last 4 days.
Samples taken with Rachel Sabre- Sunny- wind 8-10 mph
Sunny- dry- 70 degrees- light NE breeze- pelicans are gone- a few goldeneye in mid-lake- several fishermen but fishing has been very bad all summer and has now continued into fall.
Cloudy- 68degrees- several fishermen- NE wind ~8mph- light chop- some algae
Overcast- 71- NE breeze 5-8.  Lake is very high.  Almost 7" of rain in the last 7 days.
Cloudy- 70- light NW breeze- blue-green algae forming along east shore of main basin.  Much better north of the Skunk islands.
Mostly sunny- low 70s- green but no floating algae- calm
Strong winds previous 48 hours so lake is not as clear as it is normally.  Sunny light breeze
Much more algae and weeds than in the main basin.  Almost like a different lake.  Sunny with slight breeze.

Sunny- most of the weeds- primarily curley-leafed pondweed- have died back.  Lot of algae.   Very few pelicans and cormorants compared to previous years.  Not much carp action being reported around the lake.

10-15mph w/nw winds gusting to 25-30 Sat- Sun- Mon.  Cloudy- 70degrees today. lt. nw wind.  heavy concentrations of algae in some areas of the lake.  About 10 boats fishing (probably perch).  Not many pelicans or cormorants.
Sunny.  Lt NE wind.  Heavy algae bloom.
80 degrees- partly sunny.  SW winds about 10mph.  Lite algae bloom- water mostly clear- shallow bays very weedy (mostly CLP).  Only saw several fishermen out.
Sunny- west wind approx. 15- 80 degrees- slight algae bloom- CLP is dying back but still thick in the bays.  Some pelicans but did not see any cormorants.
88 degrees- calm wind- mostly cloudy.  Only 1 or 2 fishermen out.
1.5 to 2.0 inches of rain in the last week.  Calm- partly sunny- 80 degrees.  Only 4 or 5 boats out.

Partly cloudy.  NE wind around 8.  Just over 1" of rain in the last 24 hours.  Over 300 pelicans and cormorants on High Island- most I've ever seen there.  Lake is still high and dam is running at 397cfs.  Some matted CLP but not as bad as 2 previous years.
Partly sunny- light south breeze- 70 degrees.  Lots of perch fishermen and the most cormorants and pelicans that I've ever seen on the lake and schools of small ( 6"- 8") buffalo everywhere.
80 degrees- light NE wind.  About 1.5 inches of rain in last 48 hours.  Hundreds of cormorants and pelicans.  Commercial fishermen up in Rakes bay.  Only 2 recreational fishermen out.
